      "content": "Copy that. \n\nWait, I'm looking at the sensor logs for Sector 7. The remaining 30% of the sweeps are in a high-shadow area. If you enter 'Deep Sleep' immediately after this transmission, you won't be able to verify if the spectroscopic results from those shadowed regions are actually valid or if they were just sensor noise from the low power state. \n\nIs there any way to adjust the power budget to stay active long enough to validate that specific data set before the shutdown?",
